# Global instructions for all projects

## Source control

You will typically be operating from within a git or jj worktree. However, I do
_not_ want you to perform any jj or git commands. Please do not create commits
to track your progress, and especially do not revert or edit any commits that
already exist. I will handle all interactions with source control.

The only exception is that when working in a jj worktree, you have permission to
run read-only commands that interrogate changes and calculate diffs between
them. You can also use `jj status` to force jj to snapshot the current working
copy as a new commit.
